formattedAddress: 738 North Bridge Rd (Kg Glam Conservation Area)

venue.name: Masjid Haji Muhammad Salleh @ Maqam Habib Noh

tip.text: All the classics can be found here.  Oldie but goodie Rom, Samba and Stan Smith bring back memories from days gone by.
Pastamania is a great hangout for a Fri or Sat night and the joint is halal too!
There are two cafes which are quiet enough for a conversation - Dome & Maison Kayser but my vote is with MK for their breads.  The pain au chocolat is amazing - ask for warm buns out of the oven.
It is sooo good but it is soooo bad...!!!
It's a good place to watch the world go by but the double construction at the Royal Plaza Hotel and Shaw Centre makes it too noisy to enjoy the scene.  Wait a few months for construction to stop.
Say hello to Nico, he runs a tight ship and makes sure the club is in tip-top shape. Keep up the excellent work, Nico!
Sit at the bar, ask for Mas Willy the bartender to take care of you.  Frites with three sauces and nachos are hot sellers!

location.crossStreet: Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1
formattedAddress: Oakwood Premier Cosmo (Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1)

tip.text: The eggs benedict for breakfast are to die for, ask for extra hollandaise sauce on the side.  Picture is of opening night of 1st TWG tea salon in Jakarta on 21 May 2013.  Semoga sukses!

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, Level 1 Unit No. 109A (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: Take the SkyTrain to T1 and get all mesmerised by the Kinetic Rain moving sculpture
The ayam sambal matta (picture) is their signature dish but their crusted halibut (too dark to take pic) is off-menu and is just amazing!

formattedAddress: FJL Building (Jl. Kemang Raya No. 25, Bangka)

tip.text: Make sure you hang out at the pool - it's peaceful and the staff is so attentive. My favorite hotel in Jakarta!
The Johnny Andrean here is the best within the whole chain. Request for Toto to do your hair. Love the Bakmi GM downstairs!
Baguettes and croissants are best when warm and just out of the oven...simple pleasures.  Do say Hi to Nichie and Lindsay - my favorite staff there!
A slice of Paradise in this crowded island. Walk into the garden and immediately sense the increase in air quality...breathe...
The lamb shawarma looks absolutely delicious.  Not certified halal by MUIS but I do hope owners Abe and Amin will get their food to be halal at least so that they can capture the Muslim clientele.

formattedAddress: #01-K1, Ngee Ann City Civic Plaza (391 Orchard Rd)

tip.text: Soo expensive ($80 for 16 macarons) but soooo yummy.  I'm hooked on their salted caramel, of course!  Come often enough, be super nice to the staff and they may sneak in their 20% staff discount.
One of the premier shopping malls in Singapore and putting up a good fight against The Shoppes at MBS.  This is still my fav!
Come here and order the works - Royal Flush and add an extra chicken wing.  Wash it all down with fresh sugar cane from Stall No. 30.

formattedAddress: Stall 2, Adam Road Food Centre (2 Adam Rd.)

tip.text: Order the Royal Flush from the Nasi Lemak at No. 2 and wash it down with freshly-squeezed sugar cane from here!

formattedAddress: Stall 30, Adam Road Food Centre (2 Adam Rd)

tip.text: Get some ice-cold ice kacang (shaved ice with syrup) to cool off after a hot afternoon of serious Mustapha shopping!
Hole in the wall...best dosa in town. After a long day of shopping at Mustafa, hop on over and rake in the masala paper dosa served on a banana leaf no less, idli and wash it all down with teh tarik!
Poor customer service but you can get any item you can imagine here at Mustafa Centre 24 hours a day at the lowest price in town
Not the best chicken rice in town but consistently good at Orchard Road price (expensive)
Friday program: prayers here then a quick dash across the street to Victory for mutton biryani and fresh lime juice!

location.crossStreet: btwn Muscat St & North Bridge Rd
formattedAddress: 3 Muscat St (btwn Muscat St & North Bridge Rd)
